</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CF43E2F97AE0FAA2" authority="(Leydig)" baseAuthorityName="Leydig" box="[323,728,1273,1299]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrangularis">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CF43E2F97A51FAA3" box="[323,617,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leydigia quadrangularis</emphasis>
(Leydig)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CD01E2F97BB1FAA2" author="Kurz, W." box="[769,905,1273,1299]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="7 - 88" refId="ref51768" refString="Kurz, W. (1875) Dodekas neuer Cladoceren mebst einer kurzen Ubersicht der Cladocerenfauna Bohmens. Sitzungsberichte der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Wien, Abt. I. Mineralogie, Biologie, Erdkunde und verwandte Wissenschaft, 70, 7 - 88." type="journal article" year="1875">Kurz, 1875</bibRefCitation>
, which is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CAFDE2F9796FFA8B" authority="Schoedler, 1863" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CAFDE2F97DA4FAA3" box="[1277,1436,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Alona leydigi</emphasis>
Schoedler, 1863
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D65394C595273CEC6E3467BC1FEC2" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA836B24C595272CEC6E3467AE8FA1F" blockId="10.[151,1436,1272,2034]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CEC6E3467B98FAD1" bold="true" box="[198,928,1350,1376]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis of the nominal subspecies. Sufficient characters.</emphasis>
(1) A fine (small-scale) striation on valves completely absent; (2) basal spine on postabdominal claw large (as long as the claw diameter at the base); (3) setae 1 and 2 on exopodite IV with short setules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA836B24C595272CEC7E3BA78E1F9F9" blockId="10.[151,1436,1272,2034]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CEC7E3BA79E2FA65" bold="true" box="[199,474,1466,1492]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Necessary characters.</emphasis>
(4) On labral keel, setulation of anterior margin short, not reaching apex, few lateral fascicles of short setules, no setules on its posterior margin; (5) setules between setae in the middle of ventral margin short; (6) preanal margin of postabdomen without hillocks; (7) exopodite III with five large setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA836B24C595272CEC7E0557A4FF815" blockId="10.[151,1436,1272,2034]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CEC7E05579D0F9DE" bold="true" box="[199,488,1621,1647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Taxonomic comments.</emphasis>
Kotov (2003) proposed a 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CD51E0557BF2F9DF" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" box="[849,970,1621,1646]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CD51E0557BF2F9DF" box="[849,970,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. leydigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, and pointed out its possible monophyly. This point of view is confirmed by my cladistic analysis. Three consistent features are sufficient to separate two subgenera within 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CC25E0A37AB3F90D" authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1875" box="[549,651,1699,1724]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CC25E0A37AB3F90D" box="[549,651,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leydigia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At this moment, only Palaearctic representatives of the subgenus are relatively well studied (Kotov 2003; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CC9EE0C97BABF952" author="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Elias-Gutierrez, M. &amp; Nieto, M. G." box="[670,915,1737,1763]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="239 - 255" refId="ref51576" refString="Kotov, A. A., Elias-Gutierrez, M. &amp; Nieto, M. G. (2003 a) Leydigia louisi louisis Jenkin, 1934 in Neotropics, L. louisi mexicana n. subsp. in Central Mexican highlands. Hydrobiologia, 510, 239 - 255." type="journal article" year="2003">
Kotov 
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CCF6E0C97B08F953" box="[758,816,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. 2003a
</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, only a few populations are determined accurately from South and Central America and Africa. All South American, African, Asian, and Australian records (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CF80E1167A21F881" author="Brehm, V." box="[384,537,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="337 - 342" refId="ref48409" refString="Brehm, V. (1954) Marokkanische Cladoceren. Bulletin de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Rabat, 34, 337 - 342." type="journal article" year="1954">Brehm 1954</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CC26E1167AF8F881" author="Olivier, S. R." box="[550,704,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="173 - 269" refId="ref52309" refString="Olivier, S. R. (1962) Los Cladoceros Argentinos, con clave de las spesies, notas biologicas y distribucion geografica. Revista del Museo de La Plata, Nueva Serie, Seccion Zoologie, 7, 173 - 269." type="journal article" year="1962">Olivier 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CCCEE1167B81F881" author="Dumont, H. J. &amp; Laureys, P. &amp; Pensaert, J." box="[718,953,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="259 - 274" refId="ref49089" refString="Dumont, H. J., Laureys, P. &amp; Pensaert, J. (1979) Anostraca, Conchostraca, Cladocera and Copepoda from Tunisia. Hydrobiologia, 66, 259 - 274." type="journal article" year="1979">
Dumont 
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CD36E1177B53F881" box="[822,875,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. 1979
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CDC6E1167C5AF881" author="Biswas, S." box="[966,1122,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="93 - 113" refId="ref48220" refString="Biswas, S. (1980) Cladocerans (Crustacea: Branchiopoda) from Assam and adjacent hill states in North East India. Records of the zoological Survey of India, 76, 93 - 113." type="journal article" year="1980">Biswas 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B434C595272CA6FE1167DABF881" author="Smirnov, N. N. &amp; Timms, B. V." box="[1135,1427,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref53733" refString="Smirnov, N. N. &amp; Timms, B. V. (1983) A revision of the Australian Cladocera (Crustacea). Records of the Australian Museum, Supplement, 1, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1983">Smirnov &amp; Timms 1983</bibRefCitation>
) must be checked. Some of them may be dealing with members of the other subgenus, because in previous keys the main feature used to discriminate between 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CCF8E1647B7FF8CC" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" box="[760,839,1892,1917]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CCF8E1647B7FF8CC" box="[760,839,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">leydigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species (the basal spine expression) was formulated inaccurately (see discussion).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA836B24C595273CEC7E1B17D50FE97" blockId="10.[151,1436,1272,2034]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,152,371]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CEC7E1B17AB1F87A" authority="Chen" authorityName="Chen" box="[199,649,1969,1995]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="macrodonta" subSpecies="longiseta">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CEC7E1B17A06F87B" box="[199,574,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leydigia macrodonta longiseta</emphasis>
Chen
</taxonomicName>
Shou-zhong, 1992 is not a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CA98E1B17D71F87B" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1916" box="[1176,1353,1969,1994]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodonta">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CA98E1B17D71F87B" box="[1176,1353,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. macrodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CF48E1D879A0F840" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" box="[328,408,2008,2033]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CF48E1D879A0F840" box="[328,408,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">leydigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. Probably, it is a valid species, more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CA68E1D87CEEF840" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" box="[1128,1238,2008,2033]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CA68E1D87CEEF840" box="[1128,1238,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. leydigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C595272CB35E1D87DADF840" authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1934" box="[1333,1429,2008,2033]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="louisi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C595272CB35E1D87DADF840" box="[1333,1429,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. louisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having a slightly convex dorsal margin, short lateral setae, and the lateral head pores located near the major pores. But the male postabdomen (in the author’s figure) is shown as significantly narrowing distally and as lacking a distal margin. The first description (Chen Shou-zhong 1992) was lacking in detail, and a final conclusion on the status of this form can only be obtained after a re-investigation of the original material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA836B24C585273CEC7E7327BC1FEC2" blockId="11.[151,1436,152,371]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C585273CEC7E7327A7BFEFA" authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1934" box="[199,579,306,332]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Leydigia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="macrodonta" variety="louisi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C585273CEC7E73279FCFEFA" box="[199,452,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Leydigia macrodonta</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C585273CC02E7327A7BFEFA" box="[514,579,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">louisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Shen Chia-jui and Sung Ta-hsiang (1962) is a misidentification: the animal, with heavily striated valves, is not a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D314C585273CD54E7597B9BFEC3" authorityName="Schoedler" authorityYear="1863" box="[852,931,345,370]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Alona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leydigi">
<emphasis id="B963EAA04C585273CD54E7597B9BFEC3" box="[852,931,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">leydigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group.
</paragraph>
